1
00:00:04,637 --> 00:00:05,971
With <i>suminagashi</i>,

2
00:00:05,972 --> 00:00:09,141
once you drop the ink, there's no telling
how it's going to spread, huh?

3
00:00:09,142 --> 00:00:10,476
But I guess

4
00:00:10,477 --> 00:00:14,247
<i>I was trying to control things
to make it turn out the way I want.</i>

5
00:00:14,814 --> 00:00:16,615
- Sora!
- Perhaps we were

6
00:00:16,616 --> 00:00:18,817
doing nothing but forcing our own feelings

7
00:00:18,818 --> 00:00:20,519
and expectations onto her.

8
00:00:20,520 --> 00:00:21,888
We'll try once more

9
00:00:23,156 --> 00:00:24,858
to see Nene eye to eye.

10
00:00:25,525 --> 00:00:26,726
<i>Tatsuki, do you have a kid?</i>

11
00:00:27,394 --> 00:00:28,261
Yeah.

12
00:00:28,862 --> 00:00:30,630
You have to take good care of your family.

13
00:00:32,599 --> 00:00:33,700
Yeah.

14
00:00:51,117 --> 00:00:52,919
You were being followed?

15
00:00:53,987 --> 00:00:55,854
Although it could just be my imagination.

16
00:00:55,855 --> 00:00:57,823
Wait, what did he look like?

17
00:00:57,824 --> 00:00:59,658
I didn't see his face.

18
00:00:59,659 --> 00:01:02,094
I was too scared to look back.

19
00:01:02,095 --> 00:01:04,097
Have Tatsuki drop you off at home
for a while.

20
00:01:04,664 --> 00:01:07,400
He's tall, so he might at least
scare off creepy people.

21
00:01:08,535 --> 00:01:09,769
I highly doubt that.

22
00:01:10,403 --> 00:01:11,604
Look at him.

23
00:01:13,173 --> 00:01:14,207
You're right.

24
00:01:21,247 --> 00:01:23,550
Tomoki Yanagisawa.

25
00:01:25,785 --> 00:01:28,120
Hey. Shi-chan, we should head out soon.

26
00:01:28,121 --> 00:01:29,555
Okay.

27
00:01:29,556 --> 00:01:31,256
All right, Ajicchan,

28
00:01:31,257 --> 00:01:32,624
- we'll be off.
- Have fun.

29
00:01:32,625 --> 00:01:34,560
- Bye.
- Bye.

30
00:01:34,561 --> 00:01:36,695
- Mr. Tatsuki, we're heading out.
- Bye.

31
00:01:36,696 --> 00:01:37,897
Bye.

32
00:01:38,398 --> 00:01:39,899
Okay, listen up everyone.

33
00:01:40,867 --> 00:01:42,768
The time limit is 20 minutes.

34
00:01:42,769 --> 00:01:45,805
Let's find interesting materials
that are 500 yen or under!

35
00:01:48,341 --> 00:01:50,076
Soya, what do you mean by "materials"?

36
00:01:50,643 --> 00:01:52,846
Things like screws or lightbulbs.

37
00:01:53,413 --> 00:01:54,781
I'll look for a big screw.

38
00:01:56,382 --> 00:01:58,117
- A big one, huh?
- Will they have a guitar?

39
00:01:58,118 --> 00:01:59,751
It has to be under 500 yen, right?

40
00:01:59,752 --> 00:02:01,687
Yeah. I want materials for a necklace.

41
00:02:01,688 --> 00:02:03,589
- Let's go.
- Okay then, ready?

42
00:02:03,590 --> 00:02:04,490
Yup.

43
00:02:04,491 --> 00:02:05,959
Get set…

44
00:02:07,026 --> 00:02:08,027
Go!

45
00:02:28,314 --> 00:02:30,049
Is this your first time, Shi-chan?

46
00:02:31,818 --> 00:02:34,319
This project has got everyone
really hyped up.

47
00:02:34,320 --> 00:02:36,422
They're all taking this very seriously.

48
00:02:37,323 --> 00:02:40,659
There are lots of hidden gems here,
like retro machinery

49
00:02:40,660 --> 00:02:41,994
and vintage shirts.

50
00:02:41,995 --> 00:02:43,028
That's nice.

51
00:02:43,029 --> 00:02:45,264
What should I choose?

52
00:02:45,265 --> 00:02:47,000
- I'm sure you'll find something.
- Soya.

53
00:02:49,235 --> 00:02:52,471
Soya, this is 600 yen,
but can I still get it?

54
00:02:52,472 --> 00:02:56,975
But Uta, this is 100 yen over the budget,
so can you find something else?

55
00:02:56,976 --> 00:02:58,343
I want this one.

56
00:02:58,344 --> 00:03:01,747
Yeah, I'm sure. But there might be
something else that's just as nice

57
00:03:01,748 --> 00:03:02,815
so wanna go look together?

58
00:03:04,284 --> 00:03:05,217
- Okay.
- All right.

59
00:03:05,218 --> 00:03:07,554
Let's go.

60
00:03:08,454 --> 00:03:09,955
You might find something cute.

61
00:03:09,956 --> 00:03:11,457
- Yeah.
- Shi-chan.

62
00:03:12,225 --> 00:03:14,459
Look at this. Isn't this cool?

63
00:03:14,460 --> 00:03:16,628
Wow, amazing.

64
00:03:16,629 --> 00:03:18,063
This is 500 yen?

65
00:03:18,064 --> 00:03:19,265
It's 3,500 yen.

66
00:03:20,099 --> 00:03:22,835
- Then you can't buy it. Go put it back.
- So stingy.

67
00:03:23,937 --> 00:03:25,905
- So stingy.
- Stingy?

68
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:29,174
- Did you just call me stingy?
- Yup.

69
00:03:29,175 --> 00:03:31,743
- This is nice.
- This is nice too.

70
00:03:31,744 --> 00:03:34,046
- What's this?
- I don't know.

71
00:03:34,047 --> 00:03:35,447
Um…

72
00:03:35,448 --> 00:03:36,816
what will you do with all of this?

73
00:03:38,017 --> 00:03:40,285
They'll be transformed into treasures.

74
00:03:40,286 --> 00:03:41,321
‎What?

75
00:03:43,022 --> 00:03:44,323
All right, everyone,

76
00:03:44,324 --> 00:03:47,060
let's use these things to create something
you like!

77
00:03:58,371 --> 00:03:59,905
Oh no.

78
00:03:59,906 --> 00:04:02,942
- I probably won't use any yarn.
- You don't need it?

79
00:04:06,446 --> 00:04:07,980
- Nice.
- It's a little too long.

80
00:04:07,981 --> 00:04:12,317
Yeah, maybe you should cut it a little.

81
00:04:12,318 --> 00:04:15,354
- There.
- What does this line represent?

82
00:04:15,355 --> 00:04:16,655
The Keihin-Tohoku Line.

83
00:04:16,656 --> 00:04:18,091
I'm not talking about the train line.

84
00:04:21,961 --> 00:04:23,428
Gaku, what are you doing?

85
00:04:23,429 --> 00:04:27,266
This radio is broken
so I'm going to turn it into a robot.

86
00:04:27,267 --> 00:04:28,834
This will turn into a robot?

87
00:04:28,835 --> 00:04:30,102
That's a great idea.

88
00:04:30,103 --> 00:04:32,939
Shi-chan,
have you finished organizing that list?

89
00:04:33,506 --> 00:04:34,406
Yes.

90
00:04:34,407 --> 00:04:35,641
Thank you.

91
00:04:35,642 --> 00:04:37,844
Oh, I forgot. Mr. Tatsuki.

92
00:04:38,511 --> 00:04:39,879
Can I talk to you for a minute?

93
00:04:42,248 --> 00:04:43,348
YUKANAI MEMBERS LIST

94
00:04:43,349 --> 00:04:46,718
This student named Tomoki Yanagisawa
is someone I've yet to meet,

95
00:04:46,719 --> 00:04:49,422
but he's still a member here?

96
00:04:50,690 --> 00:04:53,226
He hasn't been coming for over six months.

97
00:04:53,826 --> 00:04:55,461
I wonder what the situation is.

98
00:04:55,962 --> 00:04:57,964
Should we try contacting his family?

99
00:05:00,033 --> 00:05:03,602
His membership fee
is being paid every month.

100
00:05:03,603 --> 00:05:06,939
Well, there are other students
who only come once in a while.

101
00:05:08,074 --> 00:05:09,208
How about I visit his house?

102
00:05:10,243 --> 00:05:12,077
There might be something going on

103
00:05:12,078 --> 00:05:15,381
that's preventing Tomoki
from leaving his house.

104
00:05:17,317 --> 00:05:19,152
I'll start by contacting his family.

105
00:05:24,390 --> 00:05:26,426
- Ms. Shizuku.
- Yes?

106
00:05:27,293 --> 00:05:28,728
There's something I want to do.

107
00:05:31,964 --> 00:05:32,799
TATSUKING

108
00:05:35,101 --> 00:05:36,468
DISTRICT 1
TATSUKING

109
00:05:36,469 --> 00:05:37,770
NO WEAPON

110
00:05:43,476 --> 00:05:44,877
You wanted to play a game?

111
00:05:45,445 --> 00:05:46,412
Yeah.

112
00:05:48,881 --> 00:05:51,249
- Tatsuki, you're playing <i>Palxion</i>?
- Yeah.

113
00:05:51,250 --> 00:05:54,520
I played it a little while ago,
but I haven't played it recently.

114
00:05:55,521 --> 00:05:56,855
You have no weapon.

115
00:05:56,856 --> 00:05:58,790
You're unarmed.

116
00:05:58,791 --> 00:06:01,094
Leave me alone.
Being unarmed makes me cool.

117
00:06:02,095 --> 00:06:03,295
Oh no!

118
00:06:03,296 --> 00:06:05,063
I got killed.

119
00:06:05,064 --> 00:06:06,566
You're so weak.

120
00:06:08,067 --> 00:06:09,802
I guess I need to pay money for weapons.

121
00:06:10,670 --> 00:06:11,971
Why are you playing this again?

122
00:06:13,339 --> 00:06:14,707
Because I'm searching for someone.

123
00:06:15,708 --> 00:06:16,608
Searching for someone?

124
00:06:16,609 --> 00:06:18,444
- In <i>Palxion</i>?
- Yeah.

125
00:06:19,679 --> 00:06:21,246
He hasn't been coming lately,

126
00:06:21,247 --> 00:06:23,448
but do you remember Tomoki Yanagisawa?

127
00:06:23,449 --> 00:06:24,450
Of course.

128
00:06:25,218 --> 00:06:27,019
You used to play with him.
What's his username?

129
00:06:27,854 --> 00:06:28,721
What was it…?

130
00:06:29,522 --> 00:06:30,522
Was he good?

131
00:06:30,523 --> 00:06:32,724
Yeah, he was crazy good.

132
00:06:32,725 --> 00:06:33,559
Oh, really?

133
00:06:35,628 --> 00:06:37,230
He must be somewhere in this game.

134
00:06:38,164 --> 00:06:39,731
He's usually at District 18.

135
00:06:39,732 --> 00:06:41,767
- Really? I'll go there.
- Yeah.

136
00:06:41,768 --> 00:06:44,436
Wouldn't it be faster
to talk to him directly?

137
00:06:44,437 --> 00:06:46,205
I'm trying to do that right now.

138
00:06:50,176 --> 00:06:51,710
- Hey, I think that's Tomoki.
- Really?

139
00:06:51,711 --> 00:06:52,611
- Where?
- What?

140
00:06:52,612 --> 00:06:54,447
- Where is he?
- Give me that.

141
00:06:55,615 --> 00:06:57,015
Let's see…

142
00:06:57,016 --> 00:06:58,584
Where did he go?

143
00:06:59,152 --> 00:07:00,753
- I just saw him.
- Really?

144
00:07:01,954 --> 00:07:03,989
‎TATSUKING

145
00:07:03,990 --> 00:07:04,923
Oh, there.

146
00:07:04,924 --> 00:07:06,658
- There! It's "haratomo999."
- What?

147
00:07:06,659 --> 00:07:08,193
- Is that it?
- Yeah.

148
00:07:08,194 --> 00:07:09,561
Try talking to him.

149
00:07:09,562 --> 00:07:12,063
I can't. He's on the enemy side.
We can only chat with allies.

150
00:07:12,064 --> 00:07:13,132
Oh, right.

151
00:07:14,967 --> 00:07:15,967
- Oh, crap.
- Watch out.

152
00:07:15,968 --> 00:07:17,169
- Let's hide for now.
- Yeah.

153
00:07:17,170 --> 00:07:19,237
If Tomoki is playing this game right now,

154
00:07:19,238 --> 00:07:21,374
that means he's home, right? Then I'll--

155
00:07:22,008 --> 00:07:22,842
It's a crucial moment.

156
00:07:23,543 --> 00:07:24,444
Come on…

157
00:07:26,813 --> 00:07:28,013
- - Oh, no.
- Please

158
00:07:28,014 --> 00:07:30,016
don't kill us, Tomoki.

159
00:07:30,550 --> 00:07:31,384
Oh, crap.

160
00:07:35,855 --> 00:07:36,689
This sucks.

161
00:07:39,592 --> 00:07:41,761
It's not my fault.

162
00:07:43,629 --> 00:07:46,364
Why did you log on to play that game?

163
00:07:46,365 --> 00:07:49,035
I thought we could talk more freely
within the game.

164
00:07:50,203 --> 00:07:52,804
What was the reason that brought

165
00:07:52,805 --> 00:07:53,973
Tomoki to Yukanai?

166
00:07:55,775 --> 00:07:58,044
He was bullied at his previous school.

167
00:07:58,544 --> 00:08:00,413
So he transferred schools.

168
00:08:00,913 --> 00:08:03,716
But he couldn't fit in
at his new school either.

169
00:08:05,017 --> 00:08:07,587
Bullying led to school refusal, huh.

170
00:08:08,187 --> 00:08:10,489
At first, he came to Yukanai
pretty regularly.

171
00:08:10,490 --> 00:08:12,024
But he gradually stopped coming.

172
00:08:13,559 --> 00:08:16,829
Then I wonder if he spends
all his time at home now.

173
00:08:18,130 --> 00:08:19,265
Most likely.

174
00:08:21,501 --> 00:08:22,734
Hello.

175
00:08:22,735 --> 00:08:23,668
- Hello.
- Hello.

176
00:08:23,669 --> 00:08:25,170
I'm Tatsuki from Yukanai.

177
00:08:25,171 --> 00:08:27,038
I'm Aomine. Nice to meet you.

178
00:08:27,039 --> 00:08:28,673
Thank you for caring about my grandson.

179
00:08:28,674 --> 00:08:29,941
Sorry to come all of a sudden.

180
00:08:29,942 --> 00:08:32,545
No worries. The house is a bit of a mess,
but please come in.

181
00:08:33,179 --> 00:08:36,281
Is Tomoki's mother at work?

182
00:08:36,282 --> 00:08:37,282
Yes.

183
00:08:37,283 --> 00:08:40,619
She's actually
on a long-term business trip abroad.

184
00:08:40,620 --> 00:08:41,921
I see.

185
00:08:42,488 --> 00:08:44,322
Ever since it became just me and Tomoki,

186
00:08:44,323 --> 00:08:47,159
I've become unsure of how to handle him.

187
00:08:47,660 --> 00:08:49,694
He plays games in his room all day.

188
00:08:49,695 --> 00:08:51,297
I see.

189
00:08:51,998 --> 00:08:54,666
I'm sorry for not contacting you
for so long.

190
00:08:54,667 --> 00:08:55,867
No problem at all.

191
00:08:55,868 --> 00:08:58,336
Whether they come or not
is entirely up to each child.

192
00:08:58,337 --> 00:08:59,839
So please don't worry.

193
00:09:00,940 --> 00:09:04,109
Is Tomoki
usually holed up in his room all day?

194
00:09:04,110 --> 00:09:07,212
No, he sometimes spends time out here too.

195
00:09:07,213 --> 00:09:09,180
I'm gonna kill you! Hey!

196
00:09:09,181 --> 00:09:10,783
Don't get away! Die!

197
00:09:12,218 --> 00:09:13,352
All right!

198
00:09:14,253 --> 00:09:16,655
That's usually how he is
when he's playing games.

199
00:09:16,656 --> 00:09:18,391
- I'm sorry.
- It's okay.

200
00:09:19,492 --> 00:09:21,193
There's no need to apologize.

201
00:09:23,229 --> 00:09:26,231
Games are sometimes
described as "life rafts."

202
00:09:26,232 --> 00:09:27,732
While playing to your heart's content,

203
00:09:27,733 --> 00:09:30,102
you may gradually
regain your sense of self.

204
00:09:30,903 --> 00:09:31,871
Is that so?

205
00:09:33,739 --> 00:09:34,973
Since I'm already here,

206
00:09:34,974 --> 00:09:37,209
would it be all right
if I spoke to him in person?

207
00:09:38,110 --> 00:09:39,711
- Oh… Mr. Tatsuki…
- Um…

208
00:09:39,712 --> 00:09:41,146
- Is it this way?
- Um…

209
00:09:41,147 --> 00:09:41,981
All right!

210
00:09:42,949 --> 00:09:43,983
Damn loser.

211
00:09:46,586 --> 00:09:47,720
Tomoki.

212
00:09:48,487 --> 00:09:50,690
It's Tatsuki from Yukanai.
It's been a while.

213
00:09:51,557 --> 00:09:53,392
I was wondering how you've been doing.

214
00:09:56,662 --> 00:09:57,896
Just a while ago,

215
00:09:57,897 --> 00:09:59,932
I was playing <i>Palxion</i> too,

216
00:10:00,499 --> 00:10:02,301
but got killed by you in an instant.

217
00:10:03,569 --> 00:10:07,573
Tonetaku was helping me out,
but you're out of our league.

218
00:10:11,677 --> 00:10:13,045
Can I come inside?

219
00:10:13,613 --> 00:10:16,114
I want to watch you play the game.

220
00:10:16,115 --> 00:10:17,216
You shouldn't…

221
00:10:20,219 --> 00:10:21,053
‎Sure.

222
00:10:33,766 --> 00:10:37,936
I'm going to play games with Tomoki now,
so you can go now.

223
00:10:37,937 --> 00:10:39,538
But Mr. Tatsuki…

224
00:10:44,076 --> 00:10:45,077
Man, it's a pigsty.

225
00:10:52,852 --> 00:10:53,819
These are so cool.

226
00:10:55,388 --> 00:10:57,223
- It's so lame.
- What is?

227
00:10:57,890 --> 00:10:59,425
The username, "Tatsuking."

228
00:11:01,594 --> 00:11:03,829
- Is that right?
- And you're so weak.

229
00:11:07,266 --> 00:11:11,503
I hadn't been playing that game lately.

230
00:11:11,504 --> 00:11:13,172
I'm learning from Tonetaku right now.

231
00:11:17,877 --> 00:11:18,878
You can have this.

232
00:11:21,080 --> 00:11:24,050
It's the <i>Palxion</i> sticker.
I won it at a convenience store.

233
00:11:24,684 --> 00:11:25,584
It's a rare item.

234
00:11:26,519 --> 00:11:28,587
- It's the Metallic Cannon.
- Yeah.

235
00:11:38,864 --> 00:11:42,334
Today we all went to a thrift shop

236
00:11:42,835 --> 00:11:44,536
and found some interesting things.

237
00:11:44,537 --> 00:11:47,807
Everyone used that as a base
to create all sorts of things.

238
00:11:48,974 --> 00:11:51,711
Some made dolls out of colorful socks,

239
00:11:52,278 --> 00:11:54,212
some made maracas by using

240
00:11:54,213 --> 00:11:56,582
a uniquely shaped cup and adzuki beans.

241
00:11:58,017 --> 00:11:59,051
You wanna try too?

242
00:11:59,685 --> 00:12:01,654
- No, thanks.
- Really?

243
00:12:02,254 --> 00:12:05,024
But this room is filled with
all sorts of materials.

244
00:12:06,859 --> 00:12:07,793
It's all trash.

245
00:12:09,295 --> 00:12:11,096
But it might transform
into something nice.

246
00:12:11,097 --> 00:12:12,031
No, thanks.

247
00:12:12,531 --> 00:12:13,431
- It's a hassle.
- Oh!

248
00:12:13,432 --> 00:12:15,868
This box has potential.

249
00:12:16,402 --> 00:12:17,803
This is nice too.

250
00:12:19,305 --> 00:12:20,472
Stop touching my stuff.

251
00:12:20,473 --> 00:12:22,074
But it's trash, right?

252
00:12:22,641 --> 00:12:23,476
So who cares?

253
00:12:24,877 --> 00:12:25,977
This is nice too.

254
00:12:25,978 --> 00:12:29,115
I want to make something with this.
I wish I could…

255
00:12:30,382 --> 00:12:31,350
Fine.

256
00:13:37,583 --> 00:13:38,784
What's the matter?

257
00:13:41,921 --> 00:13:43,122
Why'd you come here?

258
00:13:45,391 --> 00:13:47,293
Because I haven't seen you in so long.

259
00:13:47,793 --> 00:13:49,628
So I was wondering how you're doing.

260
00:13:51,530 --> 00:13:53,566
I just wanted to see you, that's all.

261
00:13:56,902 --> 00:13:59,839
If you're doing well,
that's all that matters.

262
00:14:00,472 --> 00:14:01,974
Only come to Yukanai if you want to.

263
00:14:04,510 --> 00:14:06,178
Aren't you supposed to tell me to come?

264
00:14:08,047 --> 00:14:10,049
I used to be like that,

265
00:14:10,749 --> 00:14:12,418
but I screwed up because of it.

266
00:14:14,553 --> 00:14:15,454
How?

267
00:14:23,696 --> 00:14:26,265
There was a kid
who stopped going to school,

268
00:14:27,032 --> 00:14:29,602
<i>and I tried to drag him
out of his room by force.</i>

269
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:31,904
<i>And it led</i>

270
00:14:33,005 --> 00:14:34,907
<i>to results that could never be undone.</i>

271
00:14:38,711 --> 00:14:39,545
You were the worst.

272
00:14:41,580 --> 00:14:42,882
Yeah, definitely.

273
00:14:44,950 --> 00:14:47,419
I was truly the worst.

274
00:14:51,957 --> 00:14:53,459
That's why I never want you

275
00:14:54,360 --> 00:14:56,095
to push yourself too hard.

276
00:15:01,500 --> 00:15:03,535
But I have to end it.

277
00:15:06,572 --> 00:15:08,107
Since it'll be almost one year.

278
00:15:10,175 --> 00:15:11,577
A year?

279
00:15:12,211 --> 00:15:14,313
Ever since I stopped going to school.

280
00:15:17,316 --> 00:15:18,350
I see.

281
00:15:21,787 --> 00:15:23,088
It looks like a face.

282
00:15:39,538 --> 00:15:40,739
I'm going to take this.

283
00:15:42,574 --> 00:15:43,575
What's that?

284
00:15:45,177 --> 00:15:46,445
A flower, I guess.

285
00:15:47,212 --> 00:15:48,080
I see.

286
00:15:48,580 --> 00:15:49,481
What's yours?

287
00:15:50,950 --> 00:15:53,719
I just slapped things together,
to make a car.

288
00:15:55,154 --> 00:15:56,689
You like cars?

289
00:16:04,430 --> 00:16:05,597
What's that?

290
00:16:07,366 --> 00:16:08,267
Dynamite.

291
00:16:19,078 --> 00:16:19,912
It's done.

292
00:16:22,281 --> 00:16:24,049
That looks cool.

293
00:16:26,018 --> 00:16:29,488
- Here, you can have it.
- What?

294
00:16:31,790 --> 00:16:33,225
Trash will always be trash.

295
00:16:34,326 --> 00:16:35,627
You think so?

296
00:16:40,432 --> 00:16:41,266
Well,

297
00:16:42,701 --> 00:16:43,535
I'll hold onto this.

298
00:16:44,970 --> 00:16:46,905
I'll get going soon.

299
00:16:48,340 --> 00:16:50,242
I'll keep practicing <i>Palxion</i>.

300
00:16:53,812 --> 00:16:54,980
Hey, Tomoki…

301
00:16:56,548 --> 00:16:58,182
- Is this--
- Hey, don't touch that!

302
00:16:58,183 --> 00:16:59,251
Sorry.

303
00:17:00,652 --> 00:17:01,954
Enough already.

304
00:17:02,454 --> 00:17:04,088
- Just get out of here.
- Sorry.

305
00:17:04,089 --> 00:17:06,158
- Hurry.
- Sorry.

306
00:17:06,725 --> 00:17:07,726
See you again.

307
00:17:25,377 --> 00:17:27,312
YUKANAI

308
00:17:42,294 --> 00:17:43,494
I'm home.

309
00:17:43,495 --> 00:17:44,896
I'm sorry I'm late.

310
00:17:44,897 --> 00:17:46,498
I'll get dinner ready right away.

311
00:18:01,980 --> 00:18:04,149
TATSUKI

312
00:18:05,484 --> 00:18:07,785
I WANT ANOTHER CHANCE
TO TALK WITH YOU AND SORA

313
00:18:07,786 --> 00:18:09,988
COULD YOU MAKE SOME TIME FOR ME?

314
00:18:20,332 --> 00:18:21,600
Hey there.

315
00:18:23,502 --> 00:18:25,336
Oh, everyone did junk art today?

316
00:18:25,337 --> 00:18:26,704
Yes.

317
00:18:26,705 --> 00:18:27,705
I see.

318
00:18:27,706 --> 00:18:31,276
Did you make this, Mr. Tatsuki?

319
00:18:31,777 --> 00:18:32,844
Yeah, but forget that.

320
00:18:32,845 --> 00:18:34,146
‎Interesting…

321
00:18:35,013 --> 00:18:37,216
You're surprisingly romantic, huh?

322
00:18:37,883 --> 00:18:38,817
What do you mean?

323
00:18:39,685 --> 00:18:40,853
Who made this?

324
00:18:41,453 --> 00:18:42,621
Tomoki Yanagisawa.

325
00:18:43,689 --> 00:18:44,989
He hasn't been coming lately.

326
00:18:44,990 --> 00:18:48,192
Yeah, so we went
to visit him at his house,

327
00:18:48,193 --> 00:18:50,863
and made things together
using scraps in his room.

328
00:18:52,064 --> 00:18:52,998
You too, Shi-chan?

329
00:18:53,499 --> 00:18:56,201
I was kicked out.

330
00:18:57,369 --> 00:18:58,937
That's unfortunate.

331
00:19:00,005 --> 00:19:01,639
So he made a car, huh.

332
00:19:01,640 --> 00:19:03,441
Yes, he seems to like cars.

333
00:19:03,442 --> 00:19:06,111
But why did he

334
00:19:06,712 --> 00:19:08,713
attach dynamite to something he likes?

335
00:19:08,714 --> 00:19:11,249
Yeah, I wonder.

336
00:19:11,250 --> 00:19:14,620
And where is this headed?

337
00:19:16,955 --> 00:19:20,425
Tomoki seemed like he was
a little on the edge.

338
00:19:21,260 --> 00:19:22,793
Is that right?

339
00:19:22,794 --> 00:19:26,398
While playing games,
he spoke pretty abrasively.

340
00:19:26,899 --> 00:19:30,568
But I was wondering if
that's how he's releasing his emotions.

341
00:19:30,569 --> 00:19:32,371
I see.

342
00:19:37,476 --> 00:19:39,945
TATSUKING

343
00:19:55,861 --> 00:19:58,197
I guess it's not that easy to find him.

344
00:20:06,004 --> 00:20:08,106
HARATOMO999 HAS INVITED YOU
TO JOIN HIS PARTY

345
00:20:08,707 --> 00:20:10,275
Oh, Tomoki!

346
00:20:12,344 --> 00:20:13,244
Okay.

347
00:20:13,245 --> 00:20:14,513
YOU HAVE JOINED HARATOMO999'S PARTY

348
00:20:15,080 --> 00:20:16,348
All right.

349
00:20:18,717 --> 00:20:21,453
Tomoki, thanks for inviting me.

350
00:20:22,721 --> 00:20:25,623
This is a team battle,
so don't hold us back.

351
00:20:25,624 --> 00:20:27,726
No worries. You can count on me.

352
00:20:32,631 --> 00:20:33,465
Tatsuki.

353
00:20:36,435 --> 00:20:40,572
Thanks to you,
I was able to kind of clear my head, and…

354
00:20:43,575 --> 00:20:44,843
I was able to make up my mind.

355
00:20:47,012 --> 00:20:47,913
What do you mean?

356
00:20:49,047 --> 00:20:51,148
- Bye.
- What?

357
00:20:51,149 --> 00:20:52,317
Wait, Tomoki.

358
00:20:56,221 --> 00:20:57,756
Oh, crap.

359
00:20:59,758 --> 00:21:01,627
I wanted to talk to him a little more…

360
00:21:02,261 --> 00:21:03,128
Who are you?

361
00:21:03,629 --> 00:21:04,730
<i>I'm part of your team.</i>

362
00:21:06,064 --> 00:21:06,898
I'm sorry.

363
00:21:08,734 --> 00:21:09,568
<i>This way.</i>

364
00:21:14,773 --> 00:21:17,643
<i>I've never seen you before.
Are you friends with Haratomo?</i>

365
00:21:18,243 --> 00:21:19,077
Yes.

366
00:21:19,578 --> 00:21:20,611
We're buddies.

367
00:21:20,612 --> 00:21:25,217
<i>Then will you be joining the "festival"
on Friday too?</i>

368
00:21:26,184 --> 00:21:27,486
Festival?

369
00:21:27,986 --> 00:21:29,254
<i>Later.</i>

370
00:21:30,122 --> 00:21:31,890
Wait, what's this festival you mentioned?

371
00:21:36,528 --> 00:21:37,429
Festival?

372
00:21:39,698 --> 00:21:41,265
Friday…

373
00:21:41,266 --> 00:21:42,701
WEDNESDAY

374
00:22:01,453 --> 00:22:02,921
What's going on?

375
00:22:03,722 --> 00:22:04,556
Huh?

376
00:22:06,224 --> 00:22:07,559
I'm just cleaning up.

377
00:22:15,834 --> 00:22:18,437
OCTOBER 15TH THURSDAY

378
00:22:21,907 --> 00:22:23,775
Hello, this is Aomine at Yukanai.

379
00:22:28,480 --> 00:22:29,680
Is that right?

380
00:22:29,681 --> 00:22:31,949
Good morning, Mr. Tatsuki!

381
00:22:31,950 --> 00:22:34,518
Tomoki's grandmother just called.

382
00:22:34,519 --> 00:22:37,288
She said that Tomoki started
cleaning up his room.

383
00:22:37,289 --> 00:22:40,258
That's a good sign, isn't it?

384
00:22:40,759 --> 00:22:41,827
Give me five more minutes.

385
00:22:43,395 --> 00:22:46,098
You're like a kid. Forget you.

386
00:23:01,413 --> 00:23:02,414
Oh, no.

387
00:23:04,149 --> 00:23:05,317
I'm sorry.

388
00:23:06,618 --> 00:23:08,086
How do I put this back?

389
00:23:35,347 --> 00:23:36,615
Mr. Tatsuki.

390
00:23:38,817 --> 00:23:41,586
Mr. Tatsuki, wake up!

391
00:23:44,289 --> 00:23:46,223
Wake up!

392
00:23:46,224 --> 00:23:47,458
What is it?

393
00:23:47,459 --> 00:23:51,496
Is this Tomoki?

394
00:23:52,697 --> 00:23:53,899
Yeah, what about it?

395
00:23:54,699 --> 00:23:55,634
I was

396
00:23:57,369 --> 00:23:59,905
his homeroom teacher.

397
00:24:00,806 --> 00:24:01,640
What?

398
00:24:05,076 --> 00:24:07,511
That's definitely you in this picture.

399
00:24:07,512 --> 00:24:10,949
His last name had changed
from Harada to Yanagisawa.

400
00:24:12,050 --> 00:24:13,919
So I didn't realize it was him.

401
00:24:15,754 --> 00:24:18,255
But if you were his homeroom teacher,

402
00:24:18,256 --> 00:24:19,891
did you know about the bullying?

403
00:24:20,725 --> 00:24:23,428
The thing is, I knew nothing about it.

404
00:24:24,196 --> 00:24:25,863
Even when he transferred schools,

405
00:24:25,864 --> 00:24:29,401
I was told that it was due
to his parents' work.

406
00:24:30,469 --> 00:24:32,404
They didn't tell the school about it?

407
00:24:33,238 --> 00:24:35,240
I had no idea

408
00:24:36,308 --> 00:24:38,643
there was bullying going on.

409
00:24:43,081 --> 00:24:44,716
Where did you find this picture?

410
00:24:45,917 --> 00:24:47,318
- In here.
- What?

411
00:24:47,319 --> 00:24:49,286
The picture was crumpled up

412
00:24:49,287 --> 00:24:51,623
and stuffed in here under the dynamite.

413
00:25:00,432 --> 00:25:01,899
<i>Thanks to you</i>

414
00:25:01,900 --> 00:25:04,302
I was able to kind of clear my head, and…

415
00:25:04,870 --> 00:25:06,370
I was able to make up my mind.

416
00:25:06,371 --> 00:25:10,075
<i>Then will you be joining the "festival"
on Friday too?</i>

417
00:25:11,776 --> 00:25:12,611
Ms. Shizuku.

418
00:25:13,678 --> 00:25:14,513
Yes?

419
00:25:15,347 --> 00:25:17,716
Friday might be some sort of a D-Day.

420
00:25:18,316 --> 00:25:19,417
D-Day?

421
00:25:24,055 --> 00:25:27,659
MUSASHINO DAIHACHI MIDDLE SCHOOL

422
00:25:38,770 --> 00:25:39,904
RESIGNATION LETTER

423
00:25:39,905 --> 00:25:41,806
I don't have the confidence
to continue working here.

424
00:25:44,042 --> 00:25:46,845
I'm very sorry.

425
00:26:09,301 --> 00:26:11,336
Ms. Aomine?

426
00:26:12,737 --> 00:26:14,239
Long time no see.

427
00:26:16,508 --> 00:26:17,475
Um…

428
00:26:18,143 --> 00:26:20,978
I have some questions about Tomoki Harada.

429
00:26:20,979 --> 00:26:22,079
Can you girls help me out?

430
00:26:22,080 --> 00:26:24,182
What is it? What happened to Tomokin?

431
00:26:24,783 --> 00:26:26,551
During second grade…

432
00:26:27,218 --> 00:26:28,186
um…

433
00:26:29,387 --> 00:26:32,157
was there any bullying going on?

434
00:26:34,859 --> 00:26:37,963
Well, I guess you could call it bullying.

435
00:26:38,897 --> 00:26:40,699
Although I don't know much about it.

436
00:26:41,199 --> 00:26:43,901
It seems like he was being teased

437
00:26:43,902 --> 00:26:46,438
on social media and in group chats.

438
00:26:48,573 --> 00:26:50,008
By teasing, what do you mean?

439
00:26:50,909 --> 00:26:53,110
Remember how he was called Tomokin?

440
00:26:53,111 --> 00:26:54,244
‎Yeah.

441
00:26:54,245 --> 00:26:56,213
But on social media,

442
00:26:56,214 --> 00:26:59,651
people were writing "kin" using
the character for "germs."

443
00:27:00,251 --> 00:27:01,286
Oh, right.

444
00:27:02,887 --> 00:27:04,889
I see.

445
00:27:05,790 --> 00:27:09,159
I had no idea that was going on.

446
00:27:09,160 --> 00:27:10,728
It's not your fault.

447
00:27:10,729 --> 00:27:14,665
It's impossible to check and keep up with
all the students' social media posts.

448
00:27:14,666 --> 00:27:16,334
Yeah, and things were normal during class.

449
00:27:18,236 --> 00:27:22,240
Do you happen to know who was
taking the lead in teasing him?

450
00:27:23,942 --> 00:27:25,809
I think it was Hiromu and his friends.

451
00:27:25,810 --> 00:27:27,478
Yeah, I think so too.

452
00:27:27,479 --> 00:27:28,947
Hiromu?

453
00:27:29,681 --> 00:27:31,782
Hiromu Hasegawa
in the track-and-field club?

454
00:27:31,783 --> 00:27:33,084
Yeah, him.

455
00:27:33,618 --> 00:27:35,020
Why do you want to know now?

456
00:27:37,555 --> 00:27:39,424
I just wanted to be aware of it.

457
00:27:40,091 --> 00:27:40,925
Thank you.

458
00:27:42,227 --> 00:27:43,094
Bye.

459
00:27:43,995 --> 00:27:46,064
Bye.

460
00:27:48,767 --> 00:27:52,637
<i>I did manage to get the name
of the student involved in the bullying.</i>

461
00:27:53,204 --> 00:27:56,206
But I haven't been able
to verify everything

462
00:27:56,207 --> 00:27:58,176
that I've heard so far.

463
00:27:58,943 --> 00:28:01,812
Then could it be that on D-Day,

464
00:28:01,813 --> 00:28:04,782
Tomoki is planning to take revenge
on those who bullied him?

465
00:28:04,783 --> 00:28:06,451
I was thinking the same thing.

466
00:28:09,087 --> 00:28:10,554
Tomorrow will mark

467
00:28:10,555 --> 00:28:14,092
exactly one year
since Tomoki transferred schools.

468
00:28:15,160 --> 00:28:16,528
One year…

469
00:28:17,095 --> 00:28:18,129
I have to end it.

470
00:28:20,799 --> 00:28:22,500
Since it'll be almost one year.

471
00:28:25,270 --> 00:28:28,073
He may indeed be planning something.

472
00:28:29,174 --> 00:28:30,240
Ms. Shizuku,

473
00:28:30,241 --> 00:28:32,944
maybe you can contact the student
who was bullying Tomoki.

474
00:28:33,745 --> 00:28:34,745
Okay.

475
00:28:34,746 --> 00:28:38,249
I'll search for Tomoki on <i>Palxion</i>
until the very last moment.

476
00:28:39,884 --> 00:28:41,585
Wouldn't it be better to go to his house?

477
00:28:41,586 --> 00:28:42,787
No,

478
00:28:44,055 --> 00:28:46,124
we can be more honest with each other
inside the game.

479
00:28:47,692 --> 00:28:49,494
I'll help you too.

480
00:28:50,161 --> 00:28:51,729
Yes.

481
00:28:51,730 --> 00:28:53,731
YUKANAI

482
00:28:53,732 --> 00:28:54,833
TATSUKING

483
00:28:56,034 --> 00:28:57,534
HARATOMO999 - OFFLINE

484
00:28:57,535 --> 00:28:59,437
Tomoki is offline.

485
00:29:02,707 --> 00:29:05,143
Shall we take turns getting some sleep?

486
00:29:05,710 --> 00:29:09,781
Sure. This is kind of like a stakeout.

487
00:29:10,849 --> 00:29:13,151
- You can sleep first.
- No, you can go first.

488
00:29:13,818 --> 00:29:14,652
Leave it up to me.

489
00:29:17,989 --> 00:29:19,724
Okay, I'm counting on you.

490
00:29:20,225 --> 00:29:21,726
THURSDAY

491
00:29:29,100 --> 00:29:30,468
You're sleeping?

492
00:29:32,871 --> 00:29:33,972
TATSUKING

493
00:29:37,308 --> 00:29:38,343
Tomoki.

494
00:29:42,180 --> 00:29:43,648
I finally found you.

495
00:29:44,349 --> 00:29:45,784
I was looking for you.

496
00:29:47,252 --> 00:29:48,253
Why?

497
00:29:49,020 --> 00:29:50,355
What's the "festival"?

498
00:29:51,356 --> 00:29:52,223
‎Huh?

499
00:29:52,891 --> 00:29:55,493
You're planning
on doing something tomorrow, right?

500
00:29:57,162 --> 00:29:59,296
It's none of your business.

501
00:29:59,297 --> 00:30:01,966
I just got a bad feeling, that's all.

502
00:30:03,067 --> 00:30:04,869
It might be none of my business,

503
00:30:06,204 --> 00:30:07,705
but don't do anything dangerous.

504
00:30:09,941 --> 00:30:11,209
Tatsuki.

505
00:30:14,379 --> 00:30:15,413
Tatsuki,

506
00:30:16,714 --> 00:30:18,383
you're on my side, right?

507
00:30:19,184 --> 00:30:20,217
Of course.

508
00:30:20,218 --> 00:30:21,319
Then

509
00:30:22,086 --> 00:30:23,288
support me.

510
00:30:25,023 --> 00:30:28,159
That will depend on
what you're planning to do.

511
00:30:30,395 --> 00:30:31,262
What a letdown.

512
00:30:33,498 --> 00:30:34,432
But

513
00:30:36,134 --> 00:30:37,302
I can say this for certain.

514
00:30:39,470 --> 00:30:41,039
If anything ever happens to you,

515
00:30:41,639 --> 00:30:42,507
I

516
00:30:43,708 --> 00:30:45,877
will risk my life
and definitely protect you.

517
00:30:47,879 --> 00:30:49,447
You're just an outsider.

518
00:30:51,583 --> 00:30:53,384
Stop spouting nonsense about how you'll

519
00:30:54,686 --> 00:30:56,854
- "definitely protect me."
- It's not a lie.

520
00:30:56,855 --> 00:30:58,956
- I don't believe you.
- I'm being serious.

521
00:30:58,957 --> 00:31:00,391
Up until now,

522
00:31:01,326 --> 00:31:02,794
no matter what happened to me,

523
00:31:03,294 --> 00:31:05,997
there wasn't a single adult
who protected me.

524
00:31:08,132 --> 00:31:09,100
I've

525
00:31:10,902 --> 00:31:13,638
always been treated like trash.

526
00:31:23,615 --> 00:31:24,549
I'm…

527
00:31:27,352 --> 00:31:29,320
definitely going to see it through.

528
00:31:31,689 --> 00:31:32,724
Tomoki.

529
00:31:40,164 --> 00:31:41,099
Tomoki.

530
00:31:46,437 --> 00:31:48,206
HARATOMO999
NO PLAYER BY THAT NAME EXISTS

531
00:31:49,107 --> 00:31:50,108
Tomoki.

532
00:31:51,509 --> 00:31:52,677
He disappeared.

533
00:31:55,914 --> 00:31:58,282
- "I'll definitely see it through"?
- Yes.

534
00:31:58,283 --> 00:32:00,517
What is he planning to do?

535
00:32:00,518 --> 00:32:04,554
I think it takes a lot of resolve
to delete your own account.

536
00:32:04,555 --> 00:32:06,623
- I bet.
- Yeah.

537
00:32:06,624 --> 00:32:08,726
How was he when he was making this?

538
00:32:11,162 --> 00:32:15,033
He said that the front of the car
looks like a face.

539
00:32:18,136 --> 00:32:21,004
Maybe he saw his own face in this artwork.

540
00:32:21,005 --> 00:32:23,107
His own face?

541
00:32:24,742 --> 00:32:26,544
Did you notice anything else?

542
00:32:27,312 --> 00:32:30,682
Did he seem scared, lonely, or sad?

543
00:32:31,983 --> 00:32:35,752
I couldn't pick up much, but he said…

544
00:32:35,753 --> 00:32:37,155
Up until now,

545
00:32:37,956 --> 00:32:39,423
no matter what happened to me,

546
00:32:39,424 --> 00:32:42,427
there wasn't a single adult
who protected me.

547
00:32:43,361 --> 00:32:45,862
It made me think
that he's harboring anger.

548
00:32:45,863 --> 00:32:48,032
- Anger?
- Yes.

549
00:32:50,568 --> 00:32:51,736
I see.

550
00:32:52,804 --> 00:32:55,006
What should we do?

551
00:33:05,416 --> 00:33:07,250
I think this flower that you made

552
00:33:07,251 --> 00:33:10,454
expresses your desire to protect.

553
00:33:10,455 --> 00:33:11,456
Am I right?

554
00:33:17,595 --> 00:33:20,698
You're the only one
who can protect Tomoki.

555
00:33:32,043 --> 00:33:34,244
YU

556
00:33:34,245 --> 00:33:37,749
I CAN MAKE TIME TODAY
BETWEEN 17:00 TO 18:00

557
00:33:44,455 --> 00:33:45,590
Today…

558
00:33:50,228 --> 00:33:52,229
- Bye.
- Bye.

559
00:33:52,230 --> 00:33:53,397
- Later.
- Bye.

560
00:33:53,398 --> 00:33:54,297
- Bye.
- Bye.

561
00:33:54,298 --> 00:33:56,566
You're Hiromu Hasegawa, right?

562
00:33:56,567 --> 00:33:58,368
MUSASHINO DAIHACHI MIDDLE SCHOOL

563
00:33:58,369 --> 00:34:00,303
Hey, Ms. Shizu!

564
00:34:00,304 --> 00:34:03,907
Sorry for stopping you like this.
Are you headed home now?

565
00:34:03,908 --> 00:34:05,609
What is it all of a sudden?

566
00:34:05,610 --> 00:34:08,879
You're not planning on meeting up
with anyone, are you?

567
00:34:08,880 --> 00:34:11,081
No, since there's a competition tomorrow.

568
00:34:11,082 --> 00:34:12,783
Oh, for track-and-field?

569
00:34:12,784 --> 00:34:16,219
My high school scholarship is on the line,
so I have to win this one.

570
00:34:16,220 --> 00:34:18,089
I see. Good luck.

571
00:34:18,856 --> 00:34:20,858
That's all. Sorry for bothering you.

572
00:34:22,260 --> 00:34:23,161
Bye.

573
00:34:24,295 --> 00:34:25,430
Be careful.

574
00:34:47,718 --> 00:34:50,054
SORRY, I CAN'T MAKE IT JUST YET

575
00:35:10,341 --> 00:35:11,241
Hello?

576
00:35:11,242 --> 00:35:13,778
Hiromu made it home safely.

577
00:35:15,379 --> 00:35:17,381
No movements here either.

578
00:35:18,282 --> 00:35:21,017
<i>You can return to Yukanai for now.</i>

579
00:35:21,018 --> 00:35:22,153
Okay.

580
00:37:12,263 --> 00:37:13,564
What do you want?

581
00:37:15,399 --> 00:37:16,467
Oh, you caught me.

582
00:37:17,235 --> 00:37:18,336
You were so obvious.

583
00:37:19,870 --> 00:37:21,705
You're terrible at being inconspicuous,

584
00:37:21,706 --> 00:37:23,474
both in games and in real life.

585
00:37:24,809 --> 00:37:26,143
Seriously?

586
00:37:28,346 --> 00:37:29,580
Why did you follow me?

587
00:37:33,284 --> 00:37:34,318
Because

588
00:37:35,319 --> 00:37:37,255
I want to know
what the "festival" is about.

589
00:37:39,991 --> 00:37:41,225
Today marks one year

590
00:37:42,560 --> 00:37:44,228
since I transferred schools.

591
00:37:48,566 --> 00:37:49,500
Today

592
00:37:50,101 --> 00:37:52,670
is the anniversary of the day
I was driven out of school.

593
00:37:55,273 --> 00:37:56,173
I see.

594
00:38:03,447 --> 00:38:07,652
It all started with light teasing.

595
00:38:08,786 --> 00:38:10,921
<i>It didn't really bother me at first.</i>

596
00:38:11,989 --> 00:38:13,490
CLASS 2-3

597
00:38:13,491 --> 00:38:14,591
TOMOKIN SHOULD BE IN CHARGE
OF THE SHOPPING

598
00:38:14,592 --> 00:38:15,692
BUT HIS GERMS WILL SPREAD

599
00:38:15,693 --> 00:38:16,660
DON'T WANT HIS GERMS

600
00:38:16,661 --> 00:38:17,661
GO AWAY

601
00:38:17,662 --> 00:38:18,795
HE TOUCHED ME AND NOW THAT SPOT ITCHES

602
00:38:18,796 --> 00:38:19,864
HIS GERMS GOT TO YOU

603
00:38:27,538 --> 00:38:28,972
WHAT? TOMOKIN IS STILL IN THIS CHAT?

604
00:38:28,973 --> 00:38:30,807
SERIOUSLY?

605
00:38:30,808 --> 00:38:32,275
GROSS, I CAN'T STAND HIM

606
00:38:32,276 --> 00:38:33,377
HIS GERMS WILL GET TO ME

607
00:38:36,514 --> 00:38:37,847
HASEGAWA HAS LEFT THE GROUP CHAT

608
00:38:37,848 --> 00:38:39,817
HARU HAS LEFT THE GROUP CHAT

609
00:38:55,166 --> 00:38:58,969
The instigator was a guy named Hiromu.

610
00:39:00,204 --> 00:39:01,705
From track-and-field?

611
00:39:01,706 --> 00:39:03,641
So you know, huh?

612
00:39:05,343 --> 00:39:07,745
The truth is, I want to knock him down.

613
00:39:08,979 --> 00:39:10,915
But I don't have the strength to do that.

614
00:39:13,984 --> 00:39:15,152
Apparently,

615
00:39:15,920 --> 00:39:19,056
he's going to high school
on a sports scholarship.

616
00:39:20,691 --> 00:39:22,326
Isn't it unfair?

617
00:39:23,027 --> 00:39:24,895
When he made me suffer this much.

618
00:39:26,831 --> 00:39:27,897
You're right.

619
00:39:27,898 --> 00:39:29,200
So,

620
00:39:30,401 --> 00:39:33,504
I decided to expose
all the evidence of his bullying online.

621
00:39:35,706 --> 00:39:39,443
Then he won't get his scholarship.

622
00:39:42,446 --> 00:39:45,916
Is that what the "festival" is about?

623
00:39:49,387 --> 00:39:50,921
That's not all.

624
00:40:00,131 --> 00:40:02,532
Oh, you surprised me.

625
00:40:02,533 --> 00:40:05,202
- Iino, is that you?
- Sorry for scaring you.

626
00:40:05,903 --> 00:40:06,904
Ms. Shizuku.

627
00:40:07,905 --> 00:40:10,440
- Funamori?
- Please save Tomoki.

628
00:40:10,441 --> 00:40:11,809
‎What?

629
00:40:19,884 --> 00:40:20,851
I'm

630
00:40:22,286 --> 00:40:23,654
going to end my life here.

631
00:40:24,789 --> 00:40:25,855
‎What?

632
00:40:25,856 --> 00:40:28,892
I entrusted all the evidence
to my friends.

633
00:40:28,893 --> 00:40:31,362
I told them to expose everything
once I'm dead.

634
00:40:32,096 --> 00:40:33,397
Then

635
00:40:34,832 --> 00:40:36,700
he'll die too, socially.

636
00:40:39,804 --> 00:40:41,639
I think that'll be good enough.

637
00:40:44,041 --> 00:40:46,477
I tell all the kids who come to Yukanai

638
00:40:48,212 --> 00:40:49,747
that they can be free

639
00:40:50,347 --> 00:40:52,216
and do whatever they want.

640
00:40:54,351 --> 00:40:55,452
But

641
00:40:55,453 --> 00:40:57,822
I say that in order
to keep everyone safe and protected.

642
00:40:59,924 --> 00:41:01,192
And right now,

643
00:41:02,626 --> 00:41:04,495
I have to protect you.

644
00:41:07,498 --> 00:41:08,799
I won't let you kill yourself.

645
00:41:10,935 --> 00:41:11,969
It's

646
00:41:13,103 --> 00:41:14,938
- already game over for me.
- Tomoki.

647
00:41:14,939 --> 00:41:17,007
I don't like dragging things out

648
00:41:18,709 --> 00:41:20,710
when I know that I've already

649
00:41:20,711 --> 00:41:22,412
- lost.
- But you still can't die!

650
00:41:22,413 --> 00:41:24,882
You say that,

651
00:41:25,549 --> 00:41:27,818
but I'm the one who has to keep living.

652
00:41:29,420 --> 00:41:31,522
Stop saying, "Don't die,"
when you can't take

653
00:41:32,156 --> 00:41:33,591
responsibility for it.

654
00:41:35,025 --> 00:41:38,094
You've probably never considered
the feelings of someone

655
00:41:38,095 --> 00:41:39,596
who's wanting to die.

656
00:41:39,597 --> 00:41:41,198
I have, that's why I'm saying this!

657
00:41:46,770 --> 00:41:48,072
Remember

658
00:41:49,540 --> 00:41:51,308
how I told you about the kid

659
00:41:52,109 --> 00:41:54,078
who refused to go to school,
and I screwed up

660
00:41:54,912 --> 00:41:56,747
by forcing him out of his room?

661
00:41:58,816 --> 00:42:00,017
That…

662
00:42:03,220 --> 00:42:04,755
That was about my son.

663
00:42:08,192 --> 00:42:09,894
Later on,

664
00:42:11,562 --> 00:42:13,797
<i>he attempted suicide.</i>

665
00:42:20,137 --> 00:42:21,772
I never

666
00:42:24,608 --> 00:42:27,545
want to repeat that same mistake again.

667
00:42:30,781 --> 00:42:32,216
So

668
00:42:34,818 --> 00:42:37,922
I swore that I would protect everyone
no matter what.

669
00:42:41,425 --> 00:42:43,027
What's that got to do with me?

670
00:42:44,862 --> 00:42:46,363
Stop pushing

671
00:42:47,031 --> 00:42:49,098
- your dreams and ideals on me.
- Tomoki.

672
00:42:49,099 --> 00:42:52,202
Trash will always be trash.

673
00:42:53,170 --> 00:42:55,573
- It will forever be trash.
- You're not trash.

674
00:42:57,341 --> 00:42:58,776
You're not trash.

675
00:43:10,588 --> 00:43:12,022
Let's go back.

676
00:43:16,260 --> 00:43:17,728
Let's go back,

677
00:43:19,129 --> 00:43:21,065
and continue playing that game.

678
00:43:41,885 --> 00:43:42,886
Bye.

679
00:43:48,659 --> 00:43:49,893
Tomoki!

680
00:43:57,601 --> 00:43:58,636
Tatsuki.

681
00:44:00,971 --> 00:44:01,972
Tatsuki!

682
00:44:06,677 --> 00:44:09,413
Tatsuki.

683
00:44:10,681 --> 00:44:12,549
What should I do? Tatsuki!

684
00:44:16,086 --> 00:44:17,153
Tomoki.

685
00:44:17,154 --> 00:44:18,155
Tatsuki.

686
00:44:19,657 --> 00:44:20,491
Answer that.

687
00:44:22,059 --> 00:44:23,227
SHIZUKU AOMINE

688
00:44:24,928 --> 00:44:26,529
Hello?

689
00:44:26,530 --> 00:44:30,366
- <i>Mr. Tatsuki?</i>
- What should I do? Tatsuki is…

690
00:44:30,367 --> 00:44:32,101
Tatsuki is…

691
00:44:32,102 --> 00:44:34,303
Tomoki? Hello?

692
00:44:34,304 --> 00:44:35,806
What about Mr. Tatsuki?

693
00:44:36,440 --> 00:44:37,274
He's bleeding

694
00:44:38,142 --> 00:44:39,042
from his arm…

695
00:44:39,043 --> 00:44:40,144
<i>He's bleeding.</i>

696
00:44:40,778 --> 00:44:43,179
Tomoki, pull yourself together.
Is anyone else there?

697
00:44:43,180 --> 00:44:45,314
No. What am I supposed to do?

698
00:44:45,315 --> 00:44:46,983
Stop the bleeding immediately!

699
00:44:46,984 --> 00:44:48,818
<i>- Can you do it?</i>
- No, I can't.

700
00:44:48,819 --> 00:44:50,286
<i>Tomoki, you can do it.</i>

701
00:44:50,287 --> 00:44:52,389
<i>Apply strong pressure to the wound.</i>

702
00:44:57,928 --> 00:44:58,796
Don't die.

703
00:44:59,463 --> 00:45:01,398
Don't die, Tatsuki.

704
00:45:06,170 --> 00:45:09,205
I had become a useless adult.

705
00:45:09,206 --> 00:45:10,239
PREVIEW OF THE NEXT EPISODE

706
00:45:10,240 --> 00:45:11,174
THIS DRAMA IS FICTION

707
00:45:11,175 --> 00:45:12,142
Subtitle translation by: Lili Morita
